// v3: Volume + Auto-Flip (ARCHIVED - approach abandoned)
// This version attempted to track S/R type and auto-flip when price broke through.
// Problems:
// - Flip logic ran every bar, causing constant type changes
// - Yellow dotted flip lines added visual noise without actionable value
// - Volume gate (not na(avgVol) and avgVol > 0) silently blocked all pivots
// - Old levels at $400 with high touch*vol scores survived trim while new levels died
//
// Key learnings:
// - Flip tracking is unnecessary if S/R is determined by position relative to price
// - Volume filter needs graceful na handling, not a hard gate
// - Trim scoring must penalize distance from current price
// - Debug mode is essential for diagnosing invisible failures
//
// This file is preserved for reference. See docs/DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md for full details.

// [Code omitted - see DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md for the specific issues and fixes]
// The key error was the volume gate pattern:
//
//   if not na(ph) and not na(avgVol) and avgVol > 0
//       relVol = pivotVol / avgVol
//       if relVol >= volFilter
//           // ... add level
//
// This blocked ALL pivots whenever avgVol was na (first 20 bars)
// or when volume data was unavailable (some tickers).
// Fix: default to passing when volume is unavailable.
